metadata.name: Quantum Folly #137
metadata.description:
This piece explores humanity's vanity and obsession with controlling natural forces. In the end we are beholden to the whims of the universe and its rules. What we think is artificial is but nature's inclination.

As an atom gazes at the world it can see the arrogant hand of mankind imposing its will. We are nature's inane creation built from imperceptible, discrete particles.

Enjoy watching the structures form. Due to the nature of the system it may take some time to complete. Once it's fully rendered you can download a full resolution image of 3508 x 4961 px by ***double clicking/tapping***. At this size the piece is printable at A3 size at 300 dpi. If you're interested in acquiring a signed print please contact @KRANKARTA.

Features include: palette, orientation, architecture, particle rules, boundary seepage and colour displacement.

Created on Chrome desktop 103.0 on 2022-07-21 in javascript and GLSL. Results on other browsers/devices may vary.

metadata.name: PolyGarden #277
metadata.description:
Polygons, patterns and flowers are mixtured in my garden. I start with a birdeye view of the garden and its geometric structure. The species diversity and the random stack of rocks, sands, fences and other objects are main structures I want to capture, in an abstract and planar style. 

Moreover, in this project, I also try to explore the representation ability of generative art. I select three elements: shape of entity, layout of palette, and stack of object location. The factors behind these elements are the balance of randomness and structure: the generative art generates the variants from randomness but restricts its chaos with structure (deterministic constraints) to represent the meaningful results. 

Variables:
- 4 layouts
- 6 texture patterns
- 15 color palette
- 3 randomness
- 2 completeness

Please be patient with drawing process.

metadata.name: Patched with Tartan #63
metadata.description:
Patched with Tartan is a generative patchwork made with p5.js. 
Evolving from my earlier work, "Patched", this new piece has 576 possible layout combinations, 17 new printed patterns on a choice of 7 new textile textures and two new woven fabrics with near infinite colour variation chosen from one of 13 palettes. 

This piece introduces a new tartan fabric which gives it its name. Due to the vagaries of generative art it is quite possible that a piece won't contain any tartan though so all holders of Patched with Tartan will receive free access to a brand new pure tartan token in a couple of weeks.

'2' to regenerate at 2000x2000
'3' to regenerate at 3000x3000
'r' to regenerate at window size

metadata.name: Kitten Fantasy #62
metadata.description:
Kitten Fantasy, by NJT

The Kitten Fantasy is a unique digital-hand-drawn kittens which can Randomly Generate new cut paper artworks.

The Kitten Fantasy collection contains Traits 6 (50 layers), and it can make your own unique NFT.

These NFTs are randomly minted, which is a chance for everyone to get a rare version.


Don't hesitate to send me DM on twitter for more info : @mahdi_njt
